title: For Sale/Trade:  Slide Fire MOD Stock
postcontent: I am selling/trading my SSAR-15 MOD stock used only one time.  This is SlideFire's newest stock and it has multiple improvements from it's predecessors.  This stock was built from the ground up for the PRECISION shooter.  Unlike the SBS or OGR stocks, the MOD stock has the capabilities of rapid fire but also when locked, creates an extremely tight fitting stock that has absolutely no play, making it extremely more accurate than those that came before. Some of the features are:*Stock adusts in six seperate positions*Can be easily swithced between Standard and Rapid Fire modes*It has an ambidextrous sling mount (QD sling mount as well) and finger rest *Comes with the extra insert that converts it to a regular style stock.  Take that insert out and put in the finger rest insert and it returns to being able to maintain the rapid fire we all love from the line of SlideFire Stocks*Has santoprene grips for better grip and more ergonical feel*Has a nice rubber butt pad, something that the OGR and SBS do not have.  (No need to tear up your shoulder just because you want to shoot +900 rounds a minute)*Extremely more accurate than the SBS or OGR stocks and is easily able to rapid fire or do a controlled 3 round burst as well as being able to quickly and effectively shoot semi-automatic. *It's for use on AR-15 rifles equipped with a carbine style buffer tube *Compatible with mil-spec buffer tubes*Last but not least (at least on this list) it makes your AR-15 resemble guns such as the SCAR and similar type rifles making the apperance of the rifle absolutely beautiful.This stock is practially new.  It comes with everything that comes in the original packaging (which I still have) and well as a letter of approval from ATF and user manual (and don't forget that it comes with the extra finger insert).GET IT WHILE YOU CAN.  The bill that is being passed around will not ban SlideFire stocks, but rather stop production of these stocks, so there are a limited number of them.  If you have not purchased one before today, you will NOT be able to purchase one from any online or brick and mortar store, making the value of these stocks rise literally every hour.  At this time, I am selling for $600, but would rather do a trade than sell.

title: For Sale:  Colt 1911, Made in 1918
postcontent: Please read the Item Characteristics for important listing details.For this auction, we have a Colt Model of 1911. This pistol is "United States Property" marked of the left side of the receiver. The 'Rampant Colt' is found on the top rear of the left side of the slide. The left side of the slide also has 5 different Patent dates. The last one is Aug. 19, 1913.The Inspector's stamp on the left side of the frame, just above the magazine release, corresponds to Major John M. Gilbert. By serial number, this pistol was made around 1918. The pistol appears to have been re-Parkerized at some time, and the hammer replaced, but we could not find any arsenal re-work markings. The wooden grips appear to be original. The magazine is after-market. There are some blemishes in the finish (see pictures). One is the circular 'ring' around the right side of the frame, where the slide release pin comes through. Overall condition is around 90+%. Bore is in great condition, but the barrel is a High Standard. This is great 1911 for a Colt 1911 collector. Good luck in the bidding.

title: For Sale:  S&W 3913 Tactical 9mm
postcontent: The Smith and Wesson 3913 is well known for accuracy and reliability. It is all metal with aluminum alloy frame, stainless slide, and stainless barrel. It has an ambidextrous safety/de-cocker lever, a slide release lever, a magazine release, and a magazine disconnect which disables the trigger when the magazine is removed. It is thin, at barely an inch wide, making it a favorite for concealed carry.The trigger is DA first shot with following shots SA. The difference between this pistol and others claiming to be double action is that the first shot is true double action. The hammer strikes every time the trigger is pulled just like a revolver. Trigger pull is very smooth with DA pull at about 10 lbs and SA pull at about four lbs. A short reset allows quick follow up shots. Comes with 3, 8 round magazines, manual and original case.
